Run Terraform
cd "C:\Projects\DevOps Project\terraform"
1. terraform init
2. terraform plan
3. terraform apply

1. init
Downloads AWS provider
Prepares working directory
Initializes .terraform folder

2. terraform plan
Preview changes before applying
What it does:
Reads your .tf files
Shows what will be created/changed/deleted

3. terraform apply
Actually create resources
What it does:
Calls AWS APIs
Creates EC2, SG, etc.
Applies everything

Note -> To destroy and to start clean -> terraform destroy

